Master of the Elements</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=matthiuscinderfist>Matthius Cinderfist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#333333>(2/27/03 11:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1861.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Call of the Arch Mage Solo/duo questions</span><hr size=1> Elementals do not summon<br>
<br>
I use burnout 5 all the time; sometimes FB if I'm feeling dangerous.<br>
<br>
If charm breaks, I am usually far enough away to be able to mez it, reapply malosinia, recharm; if you don't use your focus ring usually, use it when charming.<br>
<br>
If charm breaks while fighting a giant, I'm usually pretty screwed because the giant will summon me and both pet/giant will be kicking my ass.<br>
<br>
I've found that 2 or 3 people works better for charm groups if you can find a friend with snare or another pet class.<br>
<br>
You will die a lot learning the ropes; make friends with a BoT keyed cleric/pally <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Good luck! <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=20616">Sage Matthius Cinderfist</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Shorty Arch Convoker of <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub41.ezboard.com/bforlorn"> Forlorn</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sarelorn>Sarelorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 244<br> <font color=#333333>(2/27/03 3:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1861.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Call of the Arch Mage Solo/duo questions</span><hr size=1> Yeah, if you're going to solo, haste becomes a neccesity, otherwise your pet is too evenly matched with the mobs, and you've got to blow a lot of mana on nukes.<br>
<br>
Get a white ceramic band. Free 5pt nuke that counts as enough damage to get you your xp.<br>
<br>
If you don't have it, get Pet Discipline immediately. Not being able to stop your pet from fighting during enrage is bad. If you've got Elemental Silence, you can use that on the mob when it enrages to save your pet a buttload of damage.<br>
<br>
Like Matthius said, if charm breaks during a fight with a giant, you're screwed. Of the dozens of times I've had it happen, I managed to channel gate exactly ONCE. I was raid buffed at the time, and was low enough to have buffs stripped when I zoned.<br>
<br>
If you can, take over the camp near where Gaukr Sandstorm pops. Nice open area (although pathing is messed) where it's not too hard to pull singles, and if you get in trouble you can step on his platform to go to the courtyard...although that won't save you from a summoning giant.<br>
<br>
When your pet gets low on health, gate out and run back in. By the time you get back, he'll be healed. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=3284">Sarelorn Stonecaller</a><BR>
Arch Convoker<BR>
<a href="http://pub24.ezboard.com/bsolinvictus">Sol Invictus</a><BR>
The Tribunal</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=magnasab>MagnasAB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#333333>(2/27/03 5:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1861.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Call of the Arch Mage Solo/duo questions</span><hr size=1> All good advice here.  One thing you can try, pull with some form of malo and do no damage. 9 times out of 10 the giant will not summon you and you will have time to recharm to finish the fight or portal out to saftey. You will just want to make sure to hit the giant with a 5dd band at the end of his enarge just before your pet kills it.  I would have to say pet hold is almost a most to be effect at soloing, with out it the giants will just do to much damage with enrage and earth pets regen very slow.  One last thing always make sure your pet has DS on it and also give your pet two different weapons this will let them duel wield (learned this from a friendly chanter).      <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sahphirephoenix>Sahphire Phoenix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(3/4/03 3:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1861.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Call of the Arch Mage Solo/duo questions</span><hr size=1> Or do what I do and wait for Magnas to leave and go use his Pet that he left with weapons and FB hehehe.  &lt;3 Magnas<br>
<br>
But like they said, I go to Sandstorm name area.  You can usually find a Earth pet in that area and they all line the walls with 2 at portal.  And if Earth pet is at portal when you charm you wont get agro from its neighbor.  There is a certain way I like to start my pulls to avoid bad pathing but will let you learn that the hard like i did.   Also, when you have pet charmed he will regen slow very slow and not worth healing it (even with new PoP heal) I just gate and run back.  He will be full Health when you get back.  I have never done the Mez, Malo, Charm thing.  I just charm fight 2 giants and gate.  Is there a reason for the mez malo first?  I have never been resisted on Charm so dont know. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=540992"> Sahphire Phoenix</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
65 Arch Convoker<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub77.ezboard.com/baphoticaneverquestguild">Aphotic</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->&quot;some people are still alive SIMPLY BECAUSE its illegal to kill them...&quot;<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jaromir>Jaromir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#333333>(3/4/03 3:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1861.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Call of the Arch Mage Solo/duo questions</span><hr size=1> Duo with a cleric.  I've gone hours without either of us dying and the exp will be faster than soloing alone. If you can bribe an enchanter in the zone for some form of clarity, even better.<br>
<br>
I've had little to no problems channeling a recharm while cleric keeps me alive and allows pet to reacquire agro.  The fast heals, pacification, complete heal, and DA all make clerics great partners.<br>
<br>
